"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-seine-water-quality-dirty-paris-river-swim-2024-olympics-b1173740.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|World  The men'striathlonat theParisOlympic Gameshas been postponedafter the latest water quality tests were undertaken in theRiver Seineearly on Tuesday (July 30) morning.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain's Alex Yee was due to compete in an event that will now take place at 9.45am BST on Wednesday after the women's race.\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9800952858964819, \"rank\": 0.01976919407679957, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.8804897301839734e-13, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavy rain on Friday and Saturday exacerbated the issue while there were also concerns about the water flow after excess rainfall.\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organisers and World Triathlon said: \\\"It has been decided to schedule the men's triathlon event on July 31 at 10.45 (CEST).\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999909596227, \"rank\": 9.040283174533726e-09, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's triathlon is due to take place the same day at 8am.\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Both triathlons are subject to the forthcoming water tests complying with the established World Triathlon thresholds for swimming.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 961, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999909596227, \"rank\": 9.040283174533726e-09, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paris 2024 and World Triathlon reiterate that the priority is the health of the athletes.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1019, \"end\": 1034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999909596227, \"rank\": 9.040283174533726e-09, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tests carried out in the Seine today revealed water quality levels that did not provide sufficient guarantees to allow the event to be held.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1123, \"end\": 1128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.50204504700196e-29, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Unfortunately, meteorological events beyond our control, such as the rain which fell over Paris on 26 and 27 July, can alter water quality and compel us to reschedule the event for health reasons.\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.861244752304596e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Despite the improvement on the water quality levels in the last hours, the readings at some points of the swim course are still above the acceptable limits.\\\"\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The River Seine, France's third-longest river, extends 485 miles from Dijon to the English Channel and is divided into five parts: the Petite Seine (Small Seine) from the sources to Montereau-Fault-Yonne; the Haute Seine (Upper Seine) from Montereau-Fault-Yonne to Paris; the Travers\\u00e9e de Paris (the Paris waterway); the Basse Seine (Lower Seine) from Paris to Rouen; and the Seine maritime (Maritime Seine) from Rouen to the English Channel.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1616, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996102568115715, \"rank\": 0.0003898673783341592, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1669, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dijon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0594853720875041e-16, \"text\": \"Dijon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dijon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dijon\"}, {\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_Channel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.927936349282117e-43, \"text\": \"English Channel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_Channel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_Channel\"}, {\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.50204504700196e-29, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montereau-Fault-Yonne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Montereau-Fault-Yonne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montereau-Fault-Yonne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montereau-Fault-Yonne\"}, {\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.50204504700196e-29, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sein